    "text": "![](https://www.naukri.com/code360/problems/maximize_7064965?interviewProblemRedirection=true&company%5B%5D=Intuit&sort_entity=recents&sort_order=DESC) ![](https://static.naukimg.com/s/0/0/i/transparentImg.png)\n![Naukri Code 360](https://files.codingninjas.in/new-cn-logos-1-1711622387.svg)\n  * Learn\n\n\n  * Contests & Events\n\n\n  * Interview prep \n\n\n  * Practice\n\n\n  * Resources\n\n\nLogin\nInterview problemsView all problems\nProblem\nSubmissions\nHints & solutions\nDiscuss\n#  Maximize \nEasy \n![](https://files.codingninjas.in/yellow-spark-22969.svg)\n0/40 \nAverage time to solve is 25m \n[![profile](https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AATXAJxpCeQg9LSEKJU-ZfkfW8sRGNY47IOlFuhnLt82=s96-c)](https://www.naukri.com/code360/profile/04b87327-4a91-4d8a-9fde-ec596c8829f7)\nContributed by \nPiyush \n1 upvote \nAsked in company\n![Intuit](https://files.codingninjas.in/company-short-logo-url/28/9f2f3fbbd8df9ea24fec84404902dc39.png)\n##  Problem statement \nSend feedback \nYou have an integer ‘N’ and an array ‘X’ of ‘N’ integers. You need to maximize the value of the array, which is equal to ⅀ '(X[i] - i)^2' from ‘i’ in the range ‘[0, N-1]’. To do this, you can rearrange the elements of the given array.\nDetermine the maximum value of the array you can get after rearranging the array ‘X’ elements.\n**Example:** ```\n'N' = 3, ‘X' = [1,2,1] \nIf we rearrange our array 'X' to '[2, 1, 1]' .\nThen our answer will be (0-2)^2 + (1-1)^2 + (1-2)^2 = 4 + 0 + 1 = 5.\nFor array ‘[1, 1, 2]’ value will be equal to ‘1 + 0 + 0 = 1’.\nFor array ‘[1, 2, 1]’ value will be equal to ‘1 + 1 + 1 = 3’.\n\n```\n\nDetailed explanation  ( Input/output format, Notes, Images ) \n**Input Format:** ```\nThe first line contains an integer 'T', which denotes the number of test cases to be run. Then the test cases follow.\nThe first line of each test case contains an integer 'N’.\nThe second line contains N integers, denoting the array ‘X’ value.\n\n```\n**Output format:** ```\nFor each test case, return the maximum array value for the given array ‘X’. \n\n```\n**Note:** ```\nYou don’t need to print anything. It has already been taken care of. Just implement the given function.\n\n```\n\n**Constraints :** ```\n1 <= T <= 10\n1 <= N <= 10^4\n1<= X[i] <= 10^5\nTime Limit: 1 sec\n\n```\n\n##### Sample Input 1 :\n```\n2\n2\n1 2 \n3\n1 1 1 \n\n```\n\n##### Sample Output 1 :\n```\n4\n2\n\n```\n\n##### Explanation Of Sample Input 1 :\n```\nFor test case 1: \nFrom this array, we can have 2 arrays i.e. ‘[1,2]’ and ‘[2,1]’\nFor ‘[1,2]’ the value will be equal to ‘ (1-0)^2 + (2-1)^2’ which is equal to 2.\nFor ‘[2,1]’ the value will be equal to ‘ (2-0)^2 + (1-1)^2’ which is equal to 4.\nHence answer is ‘4’       \nFor test case 2:\nIn this case, there is only one array you can get after rearranging elements of ‘X’.\nFor array ‘[1,1,1]’ answer will be ‘1+0+1=2’.\nHence the answer is ‘2’.\n\n```\n\n##### Sample Input 2:\n```\n2\n3\n1 2 3\n3\n10 12 3\n\n```\n\n##### Sample Output 2:\n```\n11\n226\n\n```\n\nC++ (g++ 5.4) \n![Full screen](https://static.naukimg.com/code360/assets/icons/controlled-timer.svg)\n1\n2\n3\n4\n5\nlonglongint maximize(int n, vector<int> x)\n{\n// Write your code here.\n}\nEnter to Rename, Shift+Enter to Preview\nConsole \nPrev \nRun  Submit code \nNext \nSettings\nReset Code\nLayouts\nFull Screen Mode\nStart timer\n",
