    "text": "![](https://www.naukri.com/code360/problems/beautiful-index_3743983?interviewProblemRedirection=true&company%5B%5D=Apple&sort_entity=recents&sort_order=DESC) ![](https://static.naukimg.com/s/0/0/i/transparentImg.png)\n![Naukri Code 360](https://files.codingninjas.in/new-cn-logos-1-1711622387.svg)\n  * Learn\n\n\n  * Contests & Events\n\n\n  * Interview prep \n\n\n  * Practice\n\n\n  * Resources\n\n\nLogin\nInterview problemsView all problems\nProblem\nSubmissions\nHints & solutions\nDiscuss\n#  Beautiful Index \nEasy \n![](https://files.codingninjas.in/yellow-spark-22969.svg)\n0/40 \nAverage time to solve is 16m \n[![profile](https://files.codingninjas.in/avatar-1710924338.png)](https://www.naukri.com/code360/profile/549140af-3ea9-4f18-9bf5-30b06c9810f6)\nContributed by \nNihal \n56 upvotes \nAsked in companies\n![PayPal](https://files.codingninjas.in/company-short-logo-url/675/c432d22f611cbb68026f70492d2f6852.png)![Facebook](https://files.codingninjas.in/company-short-logo-url/671/005b4926e308d9f0cac091529ae09b67.png)![Goldman Sachs](https://files.codingninjas.in/company-short-logo-url/29/aeacd9c525d4781763b3e38ac94e9611.png)\n##  Problem statement \nSend feedback \nYou are given an array ‘A’ of length ‘N’. You say an index ‘i’ is beautiful if the sum of the first ‘i - 1’ elements of the array ‘A’ equals the sum of the last ‘N - i’ elements of the array ‘A’, where ‘i’ is in 1-based indexing. Now you wonder which is the leftmost beautiful index.\nNote: If you select the first index, then the sum of the prefix will be ‘0’, and if you select the last index, then the sum of the suffix will be ‘0’.\nNote: You have to print the index in 1-based indexing.\nFor example:\n```\nLet’s say the array ‘A’ = [1, 3, 1, 5], then if we select index ‘2’, the sum of the prefix is ‘1’, and the sum of the suffix is 1 + 5 = 6. Since the sum is not the same, hence index ‘2’ is not a beautiful index.\n\n```\n\nDetailed explanation  ( Input/output format, Notes, Images ) \n**Input Format-** ```\nFirst-line contains ‘T’, denoting the number of Test cases.\nFor each Test case:\nThe first line contains an integer, ‘N’, denoting the length of the array ‘A’.\nThe following line contains an array ‘A’ of ‘N’ space-separated integers.\n\n```\n**Output Format-** ```\nFor each test case, you have to print an integer denoting the leftmost beautiful index. If there are no beautiful indexes, then print ‘-1’.\n\n```\n**Note :** ```\nYou don’t need to print anything. It has already been taken care of. Just implement the given function.\n\n```\n\n**Constraints -** ```\n1 <= ‘T’ <= 10\n1 <= ‘N’ <= 10^5 \n-10^9 <= A[i] <= 10^9, for 1 <= i <= ‘N’\nNote- Sum of ‘N’ over all test cases does not exceed 10^5.\nTime Limit: 1 sec\n\n```\n\n##### Sample Input-1\n```\n2\n3\n1 1 1\n3\n1 2 3\n\n```\n\n##### Sample Output-1\n```\n2\n-1\n\n```\n\n##### Explanation for Sample Input 1:\n```\nFor test case 1:\n  Index ‘2’ is the leftmost beautiful index. The left sum is 1 and the right sum is also 1.\nFor test case 2:\n  No index is beautiful.\n\n```\n\n##### Sample Input -2\n```\n2\n6\n1 7 3 6 5 6\n3\n2 1 -1\n\n```\n\n##### Sample Output -2\n```\n4\n1\n\n```\n\nC++ (g++ 5.4) \n![Full screen](https://static.naukimg.com/code360/assets/icons/controlled-timer.svg)\n1\n2\n3\n4\n5\n#include<bits/stdc++.h>\nint beautifulIndex(int N, vector<int> A)\n{\n// Write your code here.\n}\nEnter to Rename, Shift+Enter to Preview\nConsole \nPrev \nRun  Submit code \nNext \nSettings\nReset Code\nLayouts\nFull Screen Mode\nStart timer\n",
