    "text": "![](https://www.naukri.com/code360/problems/palindromic-rearrangement_2825052?interviewProblemRedirection=true&company%5B%5D=JP+Morgan&sort_entity=recents&sort_order=DESC) ![](https://static.naukimg.com/s/0/0/i/transparentImg.png)\n![Naukri Code 360](https://files.codingninjas.in/new-cn-logos-1-1711622387.svg)\n  * Learn\n\n\n  * Contests & Events\n\n\n  * Interview prep \n\n\n  * Practice\n\n\n  * Resources\n\n\nLogin\nInterview problemsView all problems\nProblem\nSubmissions\nHints & solutions\nDiscuss\n#  Palindromic Rearrangement \nEasy \n![](https://files.codingninjas.in/yellow-spark-22969.svg)\n0/40 \n[![profile](https://files.codingninjas.in/avatar-1710924338.png)](https://www.naukri.com/code360/profile/srejanbera)\nContributed by \nSrejan \n4 upvotes \nAsked in companies\n![JP Morgan](https://files.codingninjas.in/company-short-logo-url/23/3cbb97105cf48aa8b79d89c3a3c166a0.png)![Apple](https://files.codingninjas.in/company-short-logo-url/670/9ffcf0668216c6bbd1466015b018459a.png)![Rooter Sports Technology Pvt Ltd](https://files.codingninjas.in/rooster-logo-13528.jpg)\n##  Problem statement \nSend feedback \nNinja’s Friend came up again with a new challenge to test Ninja’s intelligence. There is a string ‘S’ consisting of ‘N’ small letters. Ninja’s task is to tell whether it is possible to rearrange the string so that it becomes palindromic. Can you help Ninja to solve this problem?\nA string is said to be palindrome if it reads the same backward as forward. For example: naman, rotor, etc.\n**For Example** ```\nIf N=5 and given string S is “rtoor”, the string can be rearranged as “rotor,” which is palindromic.\n\n```\n\nDetailed explanation  ( Input/output format, Notes, Images ) \n**Input Format:** ```\nThe first line of the input contains an integer, 'T,’ denoting the number of test cases.\nThe first line of each test case contains a single integer, 'N’, denoting the length of the given string.\nThe second line contains the given string ‘S’.\n\n```\n**Output Format:** ```\nFor each test case, print ‘YES’ if the string can be rearranged into a palindromic string, else print ‘NO’.\nPrint the output of each test case in a separate line.\n\n```\n**Note:** ```\nYou do not need to print anything. It has already been taken care of. Just implement the given function.\n\n```\n\n**Constraints:** ```\n1 <= T <= 10\n1 <= N <= 10^6.\nS consists of only lowercase alphabets.  \nTime limit: 1 sec\n\n```\n\n##### Sample Input 1:\n```\n2\n5\nrtoor\n3\narm\n\n```\n\n##### Sample Output 1:\n```\nYES\nNO\n\n```\n\n##### Explanation of sample input 1:\n```\nFor the first test case,\nThe given string can be rearranged as “rotor,” which is a palindromic string.\nHence, the answer is YES. \nFor the second test case:\nThe given string cannot be rearranged as a palindromic string\nHence, the answer is NO.\n\n```\n\n##### Sample Input 2:\n```\n2\n15\nacabeececbeedad\n10\nccdecaeeba\n\n```\n\n##### Sample Output 2:\n```\nNO\nNO \n\n```\n\nC++ (g++ 5.4) \n![Full screen](https://static.naukimg.com/code360/assets/icons/controlled-timer.svg)\n1\n2\n3\n4\n5\n#include<bits/stdc++.h>\nbool palidromicRearrangement(int n, string &str)\n{\n// Write your code here.\n}\nEnter to Rename, Shift+Enter to Preview\nConsole \nPrev \nRun  Submit code \nNext \nSettings\nReset Code\nLayouts\nFull Screen Mode\nStart timer\n",
