    "text": "![](https://www.naukri.com/code360/problems/counting-sort_2663351?interviewProblemRedirection=true&company%5B%5D=Morgan+Stanley&sort_entity=recents&sort_order=DESC) ![](https://static.naukimg.com/s/0/0/i/transparentImg.png)\n![Naukri Code 360](https://files.codingninjas.in/new-cn-logos-1-1711622387.svg)\n  * Learn\n\n\n  * Contests & Events\n\n\n  * Interview prep \n\n\n  * Practice\n\n\n  * Resources\n\n\nLogin\nInterview problemsView all problems\nProblem\nSubmissions\nHints & solutions\nDiscuss\n#  Counting Sort \nEasy \n![](https://files.codingninjas.in/yellow-spark-22969.svg)\n0/40 \n[![profile](https://files.codingninjas.in/avatar-1710924338.png)](https://www.naukri.com/code360/profile/c982ae85-652d-42d4-8506-42031874f36e)\nContributed by \nAbhinav \n17 upvotes \nAsked in companies\n![Morgan Stanley](https://files.codingninjas.in/company-short-logo-url/19/49a90af13a5e7694d7ecaec75ca9e1db.png)![Samsung](https://files.codingninjas.in/company-short-logo-url/18/79184636778ed4dd720ebfe7db1965d9.png)![Snapdeal](https://files.codingninjas.in/company-short-logo-url/678/ddb217b423660064d0a5b57e0084e83c.png)\n##  Problem statement \nSend feedback \nNinja is studying sorting algorithms. He has studied all comparison-based sorting algorithms and now decided to learn sorting algorithms that do not require comparisons.\nHe was learning counting sort, but he is facing some problems. Can you help Ninja implement the counting sort?\n**For example:** ```\nYou are given ‘ARR’ = {-2, 1, 2, -1, 0}. The sorted array will be {-2, -1, 0, 1, 2}.\n\n```\n\nDetailed explanation  ( Input/output format, Notes, Images ) \n**Input Format:** ```\nThe first line contains an integer 'T' which denotes the number of test cases.\nThe first line of each test case contains an integer ‘N’ representing the length of the ‘ARR’ array.\nThe second line of each test case contains ‘N’ space-separated integers representing the ‘ARR’ array.\n\n```\n**Output Format:** ```\nFor each test case, print the sorted array.\nThe output of each test case will be printed in a separate line.\n\n```\n\n**Constraints:** ```\n1 <= T <= 10 \n1 <= N <= 5000\n-10^4 <= ARR[i] <= 10^4\nTime limit: 1 sec\n\n```\n**Note:** ```\nYou do not need to input or print anything, as it has already been taken care of. Just implement the given function.\n\n```\n\n##### Sample Input 1:\n```\n2\n5\n-2 1 2 -1 0\n5\n1 2 3 -4 -5\n\n```\n\n##### Sample Output 1:\n```\n-2 -1 0 1 2\n-5 -4 1 2 3\n\n```\n\n##### Explanation:\n```\nFor the first test case, the sorted array will be {-2, -1, 0, 1, 2}.\nFor the second test case, the sorted array will be {-5, -4, 1, 2, 3}.\n\n```\n\n##### Sample Input 2:\n```\n2\n4\n1 3 4 2\n4\n1 1 -1 -1\n\n```\n\n##### Sample Output 2:\n```\n1 2 3 4\n-1 -1 1 1\n\n```\n\nC++ (g++ 5.4) \n![Full screen](https://static.naukimg.com/code360/assets/icons/controlled-timer.svg)\n1\n2\n3\n4\n5\n#include<bits/stdc++.h>\nvector<int> sort(int n, vector<int> &arr)\n{\n// Write your code here.\n}\nEnter to Rename, Shift+Enter to Preview\nConsole \nPrev \nRun  Submit code \nNext \nSettings\nReset Code\nLayouts\nFull Screen Mode\nStart timer\n",
