    "text": "![](https://www.naukri.com/code360/problems/minimum-number-of-moves-to-get-all-keys_3208458?interviewProblemRedirection=true&company%5B%5D=PayPal&sort_entity=recents&sort_order=DESC) ![](https://static.naukimg.com/s/0/0/i/transparentImg.png)\n![Naukri Code 360](https://files.codingninjas.in/new-cn-logos-1-1711622387.svg)\n  * Learn\n\n\n  * Contests & Events\n\n\n  * Interview prep \n\n\n  * Practice\n\n\n  * Resources\n\n\nLogin\nInterview problemsView all problems\nProblem\nSubmissions\nHints & solutions\nDiscuss\n#  Minimum Number Of Moves To Get All Keys \nModerate \n![](https://files.codingninjas.in/yellow-spark-22969.svg)\n0/80 \nAverage time to solve is 25m \n[![profile](https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-Vtg-oOGaaD8/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AKF05nC2n3DtAFQwapEyJk9D8b8hmkdU_g/s96-c/photo.jpg)](https://www.naukri.com/code360/profile/9c165038-5438-41b7-b1c5-f3fab63047e9)\nContributed by \nAmbuj \n3 upvotes \nAsked in companies\n![PhonePe](https://files.codingninjas.in/company-short-logo-url/135/7fe5dd3ca91bd6fc22ba838ff2fe92c0.png)![PayPal](https://files.codingninjas.in/company-short-logo-url/675/c432d22f611cbb68026f70492d2f6852.png)![Wells Fargo](https://files.codingninjas.in/company-short-logo-url/1839/6eaeed540dff1be3cf1691c377fb311d.png)\n##  Problem statement \nSend feedback \nSome players are put inside an ‘N’ x ‘M’ matrix ‘GRID’ one by one where:\n  * ‘.’ represents an empty cell.\n  * ‘#’ represents a wall.\n  * ‘@’ represents the starting point.\n  * Lowercase letters represent keys.\n  * Uppercase letters represent locks.\n\n\nThe player to collect all the keys in minimum moves will win the game. The ninja is one of the players and needs your help to win the game. He wants you to find the minimum number of moves to get all the keys. The rules of the game are:\n  * You have to start from the starting point and move in one of the four cardinal directions.\n  * You cannot walk outside the grid or walk into a wall. You can pick a key whenever you walk over it.\n  * You cannot walk over a lock unless you have the corresponding key. For example, the key for the lock ‘A’ is ‘a’.\n  * There is exactly one key for each lock.\n\n\nFor Example:\n```\nYou are given ‘GRID’= [[“@.aA”],[“.B#.”],[“...b”]]. Then the answer will be 5.\n\n```\n\n![](https://files.codingninjas.in/getkeys1-14018.png)\nDetailed explanation  ( Input/output format, Notes, Images ) \n**Input Format :** ```\nThe first line of the input contains a single integer 'T', representing the number of test cases.\nThe first line of each test case contains an integer ‘N’, representing the number of rows in ‘GRID’.\nThe next ‘N’ lines contains a String, representing a row of the ‘GRID’.\n\n```\n**Output Format:** ```\nFor each test case, print the minimum number of moves to get all the keys. Print -1 if it is impossible to get all keys.\nPrint the output of each test case in a separate line.\n\n```\n**Note:** ```\nYou do not need to print anything. It has already been taken care of. Just implement the given function.\n\n```\n\n**Constraints:** ```\n1 <= T <= 10\n1 <= N <= 100\n1 <= M <= 100\nGRID[i][j] is either an English letter, ‘.’, ‘#’, or ‘@’.\nEach key is unique.\nEach key has a matching lock.\nAlphabets for the keys and locks are chosen in the same order as English alphabets.\nThe number of keys is in the range [1, 6].\nTime Limit: 1 sec\n\n```\n\n##### Sample Input 1:\n```\n2\n3\n@.aA\n.B#.\n...b\n1\n@BaAb\n\n```\n\n##### Sample Output 1:\n```\n5\n-1\n\n```\n\n##### Explanation of Sample Input 1:\n```\nFor the first test case, then the answer will be 5.\n\n```\n\n![](https://files.codingninjas.in/getkeys1-14018.png)\n```\nFor the second test case, the answer will be -1.\n\n```\n\n![](https://files.codingninjas.in/getkeys2-14019.png)\n##### Sample Input 2:\n```\n2\n2\n@.ba\n.AB.\n1\n@.aAbB\n\n```\n\n##### Sample Output 2:\n```\n3\n4\n\n```\n\nC++ (g++ 5.4) \n![Full screen](https://static.naukimg.com/code360/assets/icons/controlled-timer.svg)\n1\n2\n3\n4\n5\n#include<bits/stdc++.h>\nint minMovesToGetAllKeys(vector<string> &grid)\n{\n// Write your code here.\n}\nEnter to Rename, Shift+Enter to Preview\nConsole \nPrev \nRun  Submit code \nNext \nSettings\nReset Code\nLayouts\nFull Screen Mode\nStart timer\n",
