    "text": "![](https://www.naukri.com/code360/problems/split-array_2663297?interviewProblemRedirection=true&company%5B%5D=Salesforce&sort_entity=recents&sort_order=DESC) ![](https://static.naukimg.com/s/0/0/i/transparentImg.png)\n![Naukri Code 360](https://files.codingninjas.in/new-cn-logos-1-1711622387.svg)\n  * Learn\n\n\n  * Contests & Events\n\n\n  * Interview prep \n\n\n  * Practice\n\n\n  * Resources\n\n\nLogin\nInterview problemsView all problems\nProblem\nSubmissions\nHints & solutions\nDiscuss\n#  Split Array \nModerate \n![](https://files.codingninjas.in/yellow-spark-22969.svg)\n0/80 \n[![profile](https://files.codingninjas.in/profile234951a48106e184bce6465353cac9c395e80b.jpeg)](https://www.naukri.com/code360/profile/a0dfaf1a-1940-4f37-bff7-6023254eb226)\nContributed by \nParitosh \n15 upvotes \nAsked in companies\n![Salesforce](https://files.codingninjas.in/company-short-logo-url/30/794e491c9f0a68dadad41b6d36f66945.png)![Google](https://files.codingninjas.in/company-short-logo-url/13/4d8a29a3a87330e2b251970b6e6ab4b9.png)![Directi](https://files.codingninjas.in/company-short-logo-url/683/23b00b0fb929ab3e433d87c9d74d57a0.png)\n##  Problem statement \nSend feedback \nYou are given an array ‘ARR’ of size ‘N’ and an integer ‘M’. You have to split the array into ‘M’ non-overlapping, non-empty subarrays such that the maximum of all the subarray’s sum is the minimum possible. Your task is to return the minimum of the maximum of all the subarray’s sum.\n**For example:** ```\nYou are given ‘ARR’ = [7, 2, 6, 10, 8] and ‘M’ = 2. We split the array as [ 7, 2, 6] and [10, 8], the maximum of 7 + 2 + 6 and 10 + 8 is 18, which is the minimum possible.\n\n```\n\nDetailed explanation  ( Input/output format, Notes, Images ) \n**Input Format:** ```\nThe first line of input contains a single integer ‘T’ representing the number of test cases.\nThe first line of each test case contains two space-separated integers, ‘N’ and ‘M’, representing the size of ‘ARR’ and the given integer.\nThe second line of each test case contains ‘N’ space-separated integers representing the elements of the array.\n\n```\n**Output Format:** ```\nFor each test case, print a single integer representing the minimum of the maximum of all the subarray’s sum.\nPrint a separate line for each test case.\n\n```\n\n**Constraints** ```\n1 <= T <= 10\n1 <= N <= 10^5\n1 <= M <= 100\n0 <= ARR[i] <= 10^9\nTime Limit: 1 sec\n\n```\n\n##### Sample Input 1:\n```\n2\n5 2\n7 2 6 10 8\n3 3\n1 4 4\n\n```\n\n##### Sample Output 1:\n```\n18\n4\n\n```\n\n##### Explanation:\n```\nFor the first test case, ‘ARR’= [7, 2, 6, 10,8] and M=’2’ when we split the array as [ 7, 2, 6] and [10, 8], the maximum of 7 + 2 + 6 and 10 + 8, is 18, which is the minimum possible.\nFor the first test case, ‘ARR’= [1, 4, 4] and M = 3 when we split the array as [1], [4], and [4], the maximum of 1, 4 and 4, is 4, which is the minimum possible.\n\n```\n\n##### Sample Input 2:\n```\n2\n5 2\n1 2 3 4 5\n2 2\n1 2\n\n```\n\n##### Sample Output 2:\n```\n 9\n 2\n\n```\n\nC++ (g++ 5.4) \n![Full screen](https://static.naukimg.com/code360/assets/icons/controlled-timer.svg)\n1\n2\n3\n4\n5\n#include<bits/stdc++.h>\nint splitArray(vector<int> &arr, int m){\n// Write your code here.\n}\nEnter to Rename, Shift+Enter to Preview\nConsole \nPrev \nRun  Submit code \nNext \nSettings\nReset Code\nLayouts\nFull Screen Mode\nStart timer\n",
