    "text": "![](https://www.naukri.com/code360/problems/count-pairs_4529771?interviewProblemRedirection=true&company%5B%5D=Google&sort_entity=recents&sort_order=DESC) ![](https://static.naukimg.com/s/0/0/i/transparentImg.png)\n![Naukri Code 360](https://files.codingninjas.in/new-cn-logos-1-1711622387.svg)\n  * Learn\n\n\n  * Contests & Events\n\n\n  * Interview prep \n\n\n  * Practice\n\n\n  * Resources\n\n\nLogin\nInterview problemsView all problems\nProblem\nSubmissions\nHints & solutions\nDiscuss\n#  Count Pairs \nEasy \n![](https://files.codingninjas.in/yellow-spark-22969.svg)\n0/40 \n[![profile](https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-U9Idsw451ac/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/ACHi3rffFBWKWNTy7fJuYygvfa92uPeUqQ/s96-c/photo.jpg)](https://www.naukri.com/code360/profile/e359b956-9248-43b7-9239-fa643cb6e306)\nContributed by \nKAPEESH \n0 upvote \nAsked in companies\n![Tata Consultancy Services \\(TCS\\)](https://files.codingninjas.in/company-short-logo-url/885/1b107798c82fea68d11a1b7c75ee70a1.png)![Google](https://files.codingninjas.in/company-short-logo-url/13/4d8a29a3a87330e2b251970b6e6ab4b9.png)![HCL Technologies](https://files.codingninjas.in/company-short-logo-url/1067/2a70ec6d52f0e1205579203bd01102f9.png)\n##  Problem statement \nSend feedback \nGiven an array of integers ‘A’, and an integer ‘K’ find the number of happy elements.\nElement ‘X’ is happy if there exists at least 1 element whose difference is less than ‘K’ i.e. an element ‘X’ is happy if there is another element in the range [X-K, X+K] other than ‘X’ itself.\n**For Example:** ```\nIf N=3 and K=1 and array elements are [1,2,5]. \nFor A[0], A[1] is the element that lies in the range [0,2] so, A[0] is the happy element.\nFor A[1], A[0] is the element that lies in the range [1,3] so, A[1] is the happy element.\nFor A[2], there is no element that lies in the range [4,6] other than A[2] so, A[2] is not the happy element.\nHence, the output will be 2.\n\n```\n\nDetailed explanation  ( Input/output format, Notes, Images ) \n**Input Format :** ```\nThe first line of the input contains an integer, 'T’, denoting the number of test cases.\nThe first line of each test case will contain two space-separated integers ‘N’ and ‘K’, denoting the size of the array and the non-negative element.\nThe second line of each test case contains ‘N’ space-separated integers denoting elements of the array.\n\n```\n**Output Format :** ```\nFor each test case, print the number of happy elements in the array.\nPrint a separate line for each test case.\n\n```\n**Note :** ```\nYou do not need to print anything, it has already been taken care of. Just implement the given function.\n\n```\n\n**Constraints:** ```\n1 <= T <= 10\n1 <= N <= 10^4\n0 <= K <= 10^5\n-10^5 <= A[i] <= 10^5\nTime limit: 1 sec\n\n```\n\n##### Sample Input 1 :\n```\n2\n2 0\n3 3 \n3 1\n1 2 5 \n\n```\n\n##### Sample output 1 :\n```\n2\n2\n\n```\n\n##### Explanation For Sample Output 1:\n```\nFor the first test case,\nN=2 and K=0 and array elements are [3,3]. \nFor A[0], A[1] is the element that lies in the range [3,3] so, A[0] is the happy element.\nFor A[1], A[0] is the element that lies in the range [3,3] so, A[1] is the happy element.\nHence, the output will be 2.\nFor the second test case,\nN=3 and K=1 and array elements are [1,2,5]. \nFor A[0], A[1] is the element that lies in the range [0,2] so, A[0] is the happy element.\nFor A[1], A[0] is the element that lies in the range [1,3] so, A[1] is the happy element.\nFor A[2], there is no element that lies in the range [4,6] other than A[2] so, A[2] is not the happy element.\nHence, the output will be 2.\n\n```\n\n##### Sample Input 2 :\n```\n2\n3 7\n7 3 5 \n2 3\n3 1 \n\n```\n\n##### Sample output 2 :\n```\n3\n2 \n\n```\n\nC++ (g++ 5.4) \n![Full screen](https://static.naukimg.com/code360/assets/icons/controlled-timer.svg)\n1\n2\n3\n4\nint countPairs(int n, int k, vector<int> &A)\n{\n// Write your code here.\n}\nEnter to Rename, Shift+Enter to Preview\nConsole \nPrev \nRun  Submit code \nNext \nSettings\nReset Code\nLayouts\nFull Screen Mode\nStart timer\n",
