    "text": "![](https://www.naukri.com/code360/problems/palindrome-count_2409873?interviewProblemRedirection=true&page=2&company%5B%5D=Adobe&sort_entity=recents&sort_order=DESC) ![](https://static.naukimg.com/s/0/0/i/transparentImg.png)\n![Naukri Code 360](https://files.codingninjas.in/new-cn-logos-1-1711622387.svg)\n  * Learn\n\n\n  * Contests & Events\n\n\n  * Interview prep \n\n\n  * Practice\n\n\n  * Resources\n\n\nLogin\nInterview problemsView all problems\nProblem\nSubmissions\nHints & solutions\nDiscuss\n#  Palindrome Count \nHard \n![](https://files.codingninjas.in/yellow-spark-22969.svg)\n0/120 \nAverage time to solve is 30m \n[![profile](https://p.naukimg.com/jphotoV1/s244:LukcMTmy3wIfG7uwUQgEbpw/wHQkbcw6zyYBg74lxFHhdNXi1ByM7/XK)](https://www.naukri.com/code360/profile/a4adc35e-d443-4c02-98cb-30b0a1809e8f)\nContributed by \nAyush \n8 upvotes \nAsked in companies\n![Adobe](https://files.codingninjas.in/company-short-logo-url/21/abc1ca60ece68058fd182d8a8fa64086.png)![Info Edge India \\(Naukri.com\\)](https://files.codingninjas.in/asset_0000000000001387_1685987773_Infoedge.png)\n##  Problem statement \nSend feedback \nNinja loves to play with strings and anagrams. A palindrome is a string that is read the same backward or forward. An anagram is a string that is formed by rearranging the characters of the string. Ninjas have been given a string ‘STR’, and asked to find the number of substrings whose anagram is palindromic.\nDetailed explanation  ( Input/output format, Notes, Images ) \n**Input Format :** ```\nThe first line of the input contains a single integer 'T', representing the number of test cases.\nThe first line of each test case contains a string ‘STR’.\n\n```\n**Output Format :** ```\nFor each test case, print a single integer representing the number of palindromes.\nPrint the output of each test case in a separate line.\n\n```\n**Note :** ```\nYou do not need to print anything, it has already been taken care of. Just implement the given function.\n\n```\n\n**Constraints :** ```\n1 <= T <= 10\n1 <= |STR| <= 5*10^3\nThe string ‘STR’ contains small letters only.  \nTime Limit : 1 sec\n\n```\n\n##### Sample Input 1 :\n```\n2\naa\nabc\n\n```\n\n##### Sample Output 1 :\n```\n3\n3\n\n```\n\n##### Explanation For Sample Input 1 :\n```\nFor first test case :\nSubstring are: {a, a, aa}\nSince, all the substrings are palindromes.\nSo, the result is 3.\nFor second test :\nSubstring are: {a, b, c, ab, bc, abc}\nSince, all {a, b, c} are palindromes. And no anagram of {ab, bc, abc} have palindromes. \nSo, the result is 3.\n\n```\n\n##### Sample Input 2 :\n```\n2\naaa\naab\n\n```\n\n##### Sample Output 2 :\n```\n6\n5\n\n```\n\nC++ (g++ 5.4) \n![Full screen](https://static.naukimg.com/code360/assets/icons/controlled-timer.svg)\n1\n2\n3\nint palinCount(string str) {\n// Write your code here.\n}\nEnter to Rename, Shift+Enter to Preview\nConsole \nPrev \nRun  Submit code \nNext \nSettings\nReset Code\nLayouts\nFull Screen Mode\nStart timer\n",
