    "text": "![](https://www.naukri.com/code360/problems/course-schedule-ii_1069243?interviewProblemRedirection=true&page=2&company%5B%5D=Optum&sort_entity=recents&sort_order=DESC) ![](https://static.naukimg.com/s/0/0/i/transparentImg.png)\n![Naukri Code 360](https://files.codingninjas.in/new-cn-logos-1-1711622387.svg)\n  * Learn\n\n\n  * Contests & Events\n\n\n  * Interview prep \n\n\n  * Practice\n\n\n  * Resources\n\n\nLogin\nInterview problemsView all problems\nProblem\nSubmissions\nHints & solutions\nDiscuss\n#  Course Schedule II \nHard \n![](https://files.codingninjas.in/yellow-spark-22969.svg)\n0/120 \nAverage time to solve is 50m \n[![profile](https://p.naukimg.com/jphotoV1/s244:LukcMTq83QYZEr+3VwgEbpw+x3Qgbcw6zybjyra0kmkTR6gqez4HPyiE)](https://www.naukri.com/code360/profile/7e85137a-3e8d-48e7-95e3-6ba8b32d4e01)\nContributed by \nDeep \n30 upvotes \nAsked in companies\n![Apple](https://files.codingninjas.in/company-short-logo-url/670/9ffcf0668216c6bbd1466015b018459a.png)![Uber](https://files.codingninjas.in/company-short-logo-url/776/2ab7f1d4a1d4cb7376d6a1ddc96a8016.png)![PhonePe](https://files.codingninjas.in/company-short-logo-url/135/7fe5dd3ca91bd6fc22ba838ff2fe92c0.png)\n##  Problem statement \nSend feedback \nYou have been given _**‘N’**_ courses and some courses may have prerequisites. Now consider a matrix _**‘PREREQUISITES’**_ of size _**'M'**_ x 2 which represents that you must complete the course 'PREREQUISITES[i][1]' before the course 'PREREQUISITES[i][0]'.\nYour task is to return the order of courses you should take to finish all courses.\n**Note:** ```\nIf it is impossible to finish all courses, return an empty array. If there are multiple answers, return any one.\n\n```\n**For example:** ```\nInput:\n3 2\n1 2\n2 3\nThere are three courses to take. To start with, First course 3 is taken. Then course 2 is taken for which course 3 must be completed. \nAt last course 1 is taken for which course 2 must be completed. So the correct course order is [3,2,1].  \n\n```\n\nDetailed explanation  ( Input/output format, Notes, Images ) \n**Input Format:** ```\nThe first line contains two integers 'N' and 'M' representing the number of courses and the number of prerequisite pairs.\nThe next ‘M’ lines in each test case contain a matrix ‘PREREQUISITES’ containing two integers denoting a prerequisite pair.\n\n```\n**Output Format:** ```\nThe only line contains a single integer 1 if the returned order of the courses is correct, otherwise 0.\n\n```\n**Note:** ```\nYou don't need to print anything, it has already been taken care of. Just implement the given function.\n\n```\n\n##### Sample Input 1:\n```\n4 4\n2 1\n3 1\n4 2\n4 3\n\n```\n\n##### Sample Output 1:\n```\n1\n\n```\n\n##### Explanation of Sample Output 1:\n```\nThere are a total of 4 courses to take. To take course 4 you should have finished both courses 2 and 3. \nBoth courses 2 and 3 should be taken after you finish course 1. So one correct course order is [1,2,3,4]. Another correct ordering is [1,3,2,4]. \nWhen the ordering is one of the above two sets then output is 1.\n\n```\n\n##### Sample Input 2:\n```\n2 1\n2 1\n\n```\n\n##### Sample Output 2:\n```\n1\n\n```\n\n##### Constraints :\n```\n2 <= 'N' <= 10^5\n0 <= 'M' <= 10^5\nWhere ‘PREREQUISITES’ denotes the prerequisites matrix.\nTime limit: 1 sec\n\n```\n\nC++ (g++ 5.4) \n![Full screen](https://static.naukimg.com/code360/assets/icons/controlled-timer.svg)\n1\n2\n3\n4\nvector<int> findSchedule(int numCourses, vector<pair<int, int>> &prerequisites)\n{\n// Write your code here.\n}\nEnter to Rename, Shift+Enter to Preview\nConsole \nPrev \nRun  Submit code \nNext \nSettings\nReset Code\nLayouts\nFull Screen Mode\nStart timer\n",
