    "text": "![](https://www.naukri.com/code360/problems/auto-suggestion_3155171?interviewProblemRedirection=true&page=2&company%5B%5D=Microsoft&sort_entity=recents&sort_order=DESC) ![](https://static.naukimg.com/s/0/0/i/transparentImg.png)\n![Naukri Code 360](https://files.codingninjas.in/new-cn-logos-1-1711622387.svg)\n  * Learn\n\n\n  * Contests & Events\n\n\n  * Interview prep \n\n\n  * Practice\n\n\n  * Resources\n\n\nLogin\nInterview problemsView all problems\nProblem\nSubmissions\nHints & solutions\nDiscuss\n#  Auto Suggestion \nHard \n![](https://files.codingninjas.in/yellow-spark-22969.svg)\n0/120 \nAverage time to solve is 60m \n[![profile](https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AAuE7mAP5ikoSvn8cHvsVdy71ICjNdHcGDXxQq4ExJtUUA=s96-c)](https://www.naukri.com/code360/profile/cfdcf101-14e3-4bf5-9494-52e8a0a670c5)\nContributed by \nSayan \n4 upvotes \nAsked in companies\n![Goldman Sachs](https://files.codingninjas.in/company-short-logo-url/29/aeacd9c525d4781763b3e38ac94e9611.png)![Microsoft](https://files.codingninjas.in/company-short-logo-url/14/a18b52c13a74e0d83f599b2be75d593b.png)![Amazon](https://files.codingninjas.in/company-short-logo-url/2/731aacbd5ef5e7c6d6195f96525fdc79.png)\n##  Problem statement \nSend feedback \nBob had a hard time remembering the spelling of words. Alice, his best friend, decided to make a program that suggests words after every character Bob types.\nAlice had an array of ‘N’ strings ‘S’ containing Bob’s most commonly used words. She decided to suggest at most three words after each character is typed. The typed word and the suggested word should have the same prefix. If there are more than 3 such words in the array, print the three lexicographically minimum words.\nDetailed explanation  ( Input/output format, Notes, Images ) \n**Input Format:** ```\nThe first line of input contains an integer ‘T’, denoting the number of test cases.\nThe first line of each test case contains one integer ‘N’, denoting the number of strings in the array.\nThe following line contains an array ‘S’ of ‘N’ spaced strings denoting the commonly used strings by Bob.\nThe following line contains an integer ‘L’ denoting the length of the string Bob is going to type.\nThe following line contains a string ‘P’ denoting the string Bob is going to type.\n\n```\n**Output Format:** ```\nFor each test case, print ‘L’ lines containing at most three single space-separated words that the Alices program will suggest after each character of string ‘P’ is typed.\n\n```\n**Note:** ```\nYou are not required to print the expected output. It has already been taken care of. Just implement the function.\n\n```\n\n**Constraints:** ```\n1 <= T <= 10\n1 <= N <= 1000\n1 <= L <= 1000 \n1 <= Sum of lengths of all ‘S[i]’ <= 2 * 10 ^ 4.\nThere are no repeated elements in the array ‘S’.\nAll characters in ‘S[i]’ and ‘P’ are lower-case English letters.\nTime Limit: 1 sec\n\n```\n\n##### Sample Input 1:\n```\n2\n4 \nabc ab aa a\n3\nabc\n3\nna bw a\n3\nabc\n\n```\n\n##### Sample Output 1:\n```\na aa ab\nab abc \nabc\na\n\n```\n\n##### Explanation for Sample Input 1:\n```\nIn the first test case, after Bob types ‘a’, the program suggests ‘a aa ab’. After typing ‘ab’ , the program suggests ‘ab abc’, and after typing ‘abc’ the program suggests ‘abc’. \nIn the second test case, after Bob types ‘a’, the program suggests ‘a’ but after typing ‘ab’ and ‘abc’, the program suggests noting.\n\n```\n\n##### Sample Input 2:\n```\n2\n2 \ncn cnn\n1 \nc\n1\nroll\n4\nroll\n\n```\n\n##### Sample Output 2:\n```\ncn cnn \nroll\nroll\nroll\nroll\n\n```\n\nC++ (g++ 5.4) \n![Full screen](https://static.naukimg.com/code360/assets/icons/controlled-timer.svg)\n1\n2\n3\n4\n5\n#include<bits/stdc++.h>\nvector<vector<string>> autoSuggestion (int n, vector<string> S, int l, string P)\n{\n// Write your code here. \n}\nEnter to Rename, Shift+Enter to Preview\nConsole \nPrev \nRun  Submit code \nNext \nSettings\nReset Code\nLayouts\nFull Screen Mode\nStart timer\n",
