    "text": "![](https://www.naukri.com/code360/problems/minimum-maximum-value_3125971?interviewProblemRedirection=true&page=2&company%5B%5D=Microsoft&sort_entity=recents&sort_order=DESC) ![](https://static.naukimg.com/s/0/0/i/transparentImg.png)\n![Naukri Code 360](https://files.codingninjas.in/new-cn-logos-1-1711622387.svg)\n  * Learn\n\n\n  * Contests & Events\n\n\n  * Interview prep \n\n\n  * Practice\n\n\n  * Resources\n\n\nLogin\nInterview problemsView all problems\nProblem\nSubmissions\nHints & solutions\nDiscuss\n#  Minimum Maximum Value \nHard \n![](https://files.codingninjas.in/yellow-spark-22969.svg)\n0/120 \n[![profile](https://files.codingninjas.in/profile234951a48106e184bce6465353cac9c395e80b.jpeg)](https://www.naukri.com/code360/profile/a0dfaf1a-1940-4f37-bff7-6023254eb226)\nContributed by \nParitosh \n9 upvotes \nAsked in companies\n![Microsoft](https://files.codingninjas.in/company-short-logo-url/14/a18b52c13a74e0d83f599b2be75d593b.png)![Infosys](https://files.codingninjas.in/company-short-logo-url/686/2398087c932cba820ce21d86962f9425.png)![Wipro](https://files.codingninjas.in/company-short-logo-url/37361/1b8d4684e2b4c6bbe7aee42c80875427.png)\n##  Problem statement \nSend feedback \nYou are given a mathematical expression ‘exp’ consisting of only two operators ‘+’ and ‘*’. You have to find the maximum and minimum value possible of the expression by placing valid parentheses anywhere in the expression.\n**For example:** ```\nYou are given ‘exp’ = 1*2+4*5+3, here the minimum and maximum value of the expression occurs when , (1*2) + (4*5) + 3 = 25, and  1*(2 + 4) *(5 + 3) = 48. Hence the answer is [25, 48].\n\n```\n\nDetailed explanation  ( Input/output format, Notes, Images ) \n**Input Format:** ```\nThe first line of input contains a single integer ‘T’ representing the number of test cases.\nThe first line of each test case contains a string ‘exp’ representing the expression given.\n\n```\n**Output Format:** ```\nFor each test case, print two space-separated integers representing the maximum and minimum value of equations respectively.\nPrint a separate line for each test case.\n\n```\n\n**Constraints:** ```\n1 <= T <= 10\n1 <= |exp| <= 100\nTime Limit: 1 sec\n\n```\n**Note :** ```\nYou do not need to print anything. It has already been taken care of. Just implement the given function. \n\n```\n\n##### Sample Input 1:\n```\n2\n1*2+4*5+3\n2*3+4+1*5\n\n```\n\n##### Sample Output 1:\n```\n25 48\n15 80\n\n```\n\n##### Explanation:\n```\nFor the first test case, ‘exp’ = 1*2+4*5+3, here the minimum and maximum values of the expression occurs when , (1*2) + (4*5) + 3 = 25, and 1*(2 + 4) *(5 + 3) = 48. Hence the answer is [25, 48]\nFor the second test case, ‘exp’ = 2*3+4+1*5, here the minimum and maximum values of the expression occur when, (2*3) + 4 + (1*5) = 15, and 2*(3 + 4 + 1)*5 = 80. Hence the answer is [15, 80].\n\n```\n\n##### Sample input 2:\n```\n2\n2*3+4\n2*3+1*5*4\n\n```\n\n##### Sample Output 2:\n```\n10 14\n26 160\n\n```\n\nC++ (g++ 5.4) \n![Full screen](https://static.naukimg.com/code360/assets/icons/controlled-timer.svg)\n1\n2\n3\n4\n#include<bits/stdc++.h>\nvector<int> minMaxValue(string exp){\n// Write your code here.\n}\nEnter to Rename, Shift+Enter to Preview\nConsole \nPrev \nRun  Submit code \nNext \nSettings\nReset Code\nLayouts\nFull Screen Mode\nStart timer\n",
