    "text": "![](https://www.naukri.com/code360/problems/partition-array_3146848?interviewProblemRedirection=true&page=2&company%5B%5D=Microsoft&sort_entity=recents&sort_order=DESC) ![](https://static.naukimg.com/s/0/0/i/transparentImg.png)\n![Naukri Code 360](https://files.codingninjas.in/new-cn-logos-1-1711622387.svg)\n  * Learn\n\n\n  * Contests & Events\n\n\n  * Interview prep \n\n\n  * Practice\n\n\n  * Resources\n\n\nLogin\nInterview problemsView all problems\nProblem\nSubmissions\nHints & solutions\nDiscuss\n#  Partition Array \nModerate \n![](https://files.codingninjas.in/yellow-spark-22969.svg)\n0/80 \n[![profile](https://files.codingninjas.in/profile234951a48106e184bce6465353cac9c395e80b.jpeg)](https://www.naukri.com/code360/profile/a0dfaf1a-1940-4f37-bff7-6023254eb226)\nContributed by \nParitosh \n4 upvotes \nAsked in companies\n![Microsoft](https://files.codingninjas.in/company-short-logo-url/14/a18b52c13a74e0d83f599b2be75d593b.png)![Grab](https://files.codingninjas.in/company-short-logo-url/1158/1d505241ba9b4162117f7021908ccd39.png)![MakeMyTrip](https://files.codingninjas.in/company-short-logo-url/680/cfb77bef9d74a0a4cf52102daed7bffa.png)\n##  Problem statement \nSend feedback \nYou are given an array, ‘arr’, your task is to partition the array into such a way that, that all the elements in the left half of the array are smaller than or equal to all the elements in the right half the array. Each partition should have at least one element. You have to return the smallest length of the left partition possible.\nNote:\n```\nThe left half of the array must be the smallest possible.\nIf there is no partition return the size of the array.\n\n```\n**For example:** ```\nYou are given, ‘arr’ = [8, 3, 1, 4, 9, 10], this array can be partitioned at index ‘3’ so the left array is [8, 3, 1, 4] and the right array is [9, 10]. Hence the answer is 4.\n\n```\n\nDetailed explanation  ( Input/output format, Notes, Images ) \n**Input Format:** ```\nThe first line of input contains a single integer ‘T’ representing the number of test cases.\nThe first line of each test case contains a single integer ‘N’ representing the size of the array.\nThe second line of each test case contains ‘N’ space-separated integers representing the elements of the array.\n\n```\n**Output Format:** ```\nFor each test case print a single integer representing the number of elements in the left half of the array.\nFor each test case, print a single integer.\n\n```\n\n###### Constraints:\n```\n1 <= T <= 10\n1 <= N <= 10^6\n1 <= arr[i] <= 10^9\nTime Limit: 1 sec\n\n```\n\n##### Sample Input 1\n```\n2\n6\n8 3 1 4 9 10\n6\n5 4 3 2 1 10\n\n```\n\n##### Sample Output 2\n```\n4\n5\n\n```\n\n##### Explanation:\n```\nFor the first test case, ‘arr’ = [8,3, 1, 4, 9, 10], this array can be partitioned at index ‘3’ so the left array is [8, 3, 1, 4] and the right array is [9, 10]. Hence the answer is 4.\nFor the second test case, ‘arr’ = [5, 4, 3, 2, 1, 10], this array can be partitioned at index ‘4’ so the left array is [5, 4, 3, 2, 1] and the right array is [10]. Hence the answer is 5.\n\n```\n\n##### Sample Input 2:\n```\n2\n3\n3 1 4\n4\n1 2 3 4 5\n\n```\n\n##### Sample Output 2:\n```\n2\n1\n\n```\n\nC++ (g++ 5.4) \n![Full screen](https://static.naukimg.com/code360/assets/icons/controlled-timer.svg)\n1\n2\n3\n4\n#include<bits/stdc++.h>\nint partitionArray(vector<int> &arr){\n// Write your code here.\n}\nEnter to Rename, Shift+Enter to Preview\nConsole \nPrev \nRun  Submit code \nNext \nSettings\nReset Code\nLayouts\nFull Screen Mode\nStart timer\n",
