    "text": "![](https://www.naukri.com/code360/problems/page-faults_2826682?interviewProblemRedirection=true&page=2&company%5B%5D=Microsoft&sort_entity=recents&sort_order=DESC) ![](https://static.naukimg.com/s/0/0/i/transparentImg.png)\n![Naukri Code 360](https://files.codingninjas.in/new-cn-logos-1-1711622387.svg)\n  * Learn\n\n\n  * Contests & Events\n\n\n  * Interview prep \n\n\n  * Practice\n\n\n  * Resources\n\n\nLogin\nInterview problemsView all problems\nProblem\nSubmissions\nHints & solutions\nDiscuss\n#  Page Faults \nModerate \n![](https://files.codingninjas.in/yellow-spark-22969.svg)\n0/80 \nAverage time to solve is 30m \n[![profile](https://files.codingninjas.in/avatar-1710924338.png)](https://www.naukri.com/code360/profile/549140af-3ea9-4f18-9bf5-30b06c9810f6)\nContributed by \nNihal \n7 upvotes \nAsked in companies\n![Tata 1mg](https://files.codingninjas.in/company-short-logo-url/1783/646668a7935067735bd3e6ad40ee2096.png)![Expedia Group](https://files.codingninjas.in/company-short-logo-url/2091/96021e4c6a6c1850c28a9ab02cac7e10.png)![Microsoft](https://files.codingninjas.in/company-short-logo-url/14/a18b52c13a74e0d83f599b2be75d593b.png)\n##  Problem statement \nSend feedback \nIn computing, a page fault is an exception for the memory management unit (MMU) when a process accesses a memory page without proper preparations.\nPage replacement algorithm is needed to decide which page needs to be replaced when the new page comes in. Whenever a new page is referred to and is not present in memory, the page fault occurs, and the Operating System replaces one of the existing pages with a newly needed page.\nYou have given a sequence of pages in an array ‘Pages’ of length **_‘N’_** and memory capacity **_‘C’_**. You have to find the number of page faults using the Least Recently Used (LRU) Algorithm. Initially, memory doesn't contain any pages.\n**For example:** ```\n'N' = 7, 'C' = 4, pages = [1, 2, 1, 4, 2, 3, 5].\nFor the first four pages, memory allocated with four pages, {1, 2, 1, 4}, page fault = 3.\nFor fifth, page number 2 is required, which is already present, page fault = 3.\nThen, page number 3 is required, replaces LRU 2, page fault = 4.\nThen, page number 5 is required, replaces LRU 1, page fault = 5.\nThe total page fault is 5.\n\n```\n\nDetailed explanation  ( Input/output format, Notes, Images ) \n**Input Format-** ```\nThe first line contains two space-separated integers, ‘N’ and ‘C’.\nThe next line contains the array ‘Pages’ of the length ‘N’, denoting the page sequences.\n\n```\n**Output Format-** ```\nThe only line contains a single integer denoting the total number of page faults.\n\n```\n**Note :** ```\nYou don’t need to print anything. It has already been taken care of. Just implement the given function.\n\n```\n\n##### Sample Input-1\n```\n4 3\n1 3 2 1\n\n```\n\n##### Sample Output-1\n```\n3\n\n```\n\n##### Explanation for Sample Input 1:\n```\nMemory allocated with three pages, {1, 3, 2}. \nHence total page faults = 3.\nThen, Page number '1' is required, which is already present. Hence total page faults = 3 + 0 = 3.\n\n```\n\n##### Sample Input-2\n```\n9 4\n5 6 1 3 2 4 1 6 5\n\n```\n\n##### Sample Output-2\n```\n8\n\n```\n\n##### Constraints -:\n```\n1 <= ‘N’ <= 10^5\n0 <= ‘C’ <= 10^5\n1 <= Pages[i] <= ‘N’, for 1 <= i <= ‘N’\nTime Limit: 1 sec\n\n```\n\nC++ (g++ 5.4) \n![Full screen](https://static.naukimg.com/code360/assets/icons/controlled-timer.svg)\n1\n2\n3\n4\nint pageFaults(int C, vector<int> Pages)\n{\n// Write your code here.\n}\nEnter to Rename, Shift+Enter to Preview\nConsole \nPrev \nRun  Submit code \nNext \nSettings\nReset Code\nLayouts\nFull Screen Mode\nStart timer\n",
