    "text": "![](https://www.naukri.com/code360/problems/nearestpallindrome_1235208?interviewProblemRedirection=true&page=2&company%5B%5D=Morgan+Stanley&sort_entity=recents&sort_order=DESC) ![](https://static.naukimg.com/s/0/0/i/transparentImg.png)\n![Naukri Code 360](https://files.codingninjas.in/new-cn-logos-1-1711622387.svg)\n  * Learn\n\n\n  * Contests & Events\n\n\n  * Interview prep \n\n\n  * Practice\n\n\n  * Resources\n\n\nLogin\nInterview problemsView all problems\nProblem\nSubmissions\nHints & solutions\nDiscuss\n#  Nearest Pallindrome \nModerate \n![](https://files.codingninjas.in/yellow-spark-22969.svg)\n0/80 \nAverage time to solve is 30m \n[![profile](https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-Vtg-oOGaaD8/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AKF05nC2n3DtAFQwapEyJk9D8b8hmkdU_g/s96-c/photo.jpg)](https://www.naukri.com/code360/profile/9c165038-5438-41b7-b1c5-f3fab63047e9)\nContributed by \nAmbuj \n3 upvotes \nAsked in companies\n![eBay](https://files.codingninjas.in/72e184150c7502468fbe3f4ae72b0d92.png)![Apple](https://files.codingninjas.in/company-short-logo-url/670/9ffcf0668216c6bbd1466015b018459a.png)![Red Hat](https://files.codingninjas.in/33f6714d08981862d3741c594ce77ae3.png)\n##  Problem statement \nSend feedback \nYou have been given a string ‘S' representing a number. Your task is to find the closest palindromic number from this integer represented by 'S'. The closest number is defined as the one for which the absolute difference between the given integer represented by 'S' and the palindrome number is minimum. If more than one number have the same difference then return the smaller integer.\nExample:\n```\nLet 'S' is 121. Then the nearest integers are 111 and 131 which are palindrome. Both have the same absolute difference but 111 is smaller. Hence 111 is the answer.\n\n```\n\nDetailed explanation  ( Input/output format, Notes, Images ) \n**Input Format:** ```\nThe first line of input contains an integer ‘T’ denoting the number of test cases.\nThe first and the only line of each case contains a single string ‘S’ denoting the integer.\n\n```\n**Output Format:** ```\nFor each test case, return the closest palindrome number from 'S'.\nThe output of each test case will be printed in a separate line.\n\n```\n**Note:** ```\nYou are not required to print the expected output, it has already been taken care of. Just implement the function.\n\n```\n\n**Constraints:** ```\n1 <= T <= 50\n0 <= No of digits in ‘S’ <= 18\nTime Limit: 1 sec\n\n```\n\n##### Sample Input 1\n```\n2\n131\n159\n\n```\n\n###### Sample Output 1:\n```\n121\n161\nExplanation:-\nFor the First Case:-\nThe palindrome just greater than 131 is 141\nThe palindrome just smaller than 131 is 121.\nBoth have the same absolute difference but 121 is smaller than 141 hence 121 is the answer.\nFor the Second Case:-\n161 is the nearest palindrome.\n\n```\n\n##### Sample Input 2\n```\n2\n121\n101\n\n```\n\n##### Sample Output 2\n```\n111\n99\n\n```\n\nC++ (g++ 5.4) \n![Full screen](https://static.naukimg.com/code360/assets/icons/controlled-timer.svg)\n1\n2\n3\n4\n5\n#include<bits/stdc++.h>\nstring nearestPallindrome(string s)\n{\n// Write your code here.\n}\nEnter to Rename, Shift+Enter to Preview\nConsole \nPrev \nRun  Submit code \nNext \nSettings\nReset Code\nLayouts\nFull Screen Mode\nStart timer\n",
