    "text": "![](https://www.naukri.com/code360/problems/magic-index_1199229?interviewProblemRedirection=true&page=2&company%5B%5D=PayPal&sort_entity=recents&sort_order=DESC) ![](https://static.naukimg.com/s/0/0/i/transparentImg.png)\n![Naukri Code 360](https://files.codingninjas.in/new-cn-logos-1-1711622387.svg)\n  * Learn\n\n\n  * Contests & Events\n\n\n  * Interview prep \n\n\n  * Practice\n\n\n  * Resources\n\n\nLogin\nInterview problemsView all problems\nProblem\nSubmissions\nHints & solutions\nDiscuss\n#  Magic Index \nEasy \n![](https://files.codingninjas.in/yellow-spark-22969.svg)\n0/40 \nAverage time to solve is 20m \n[![profile](https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-ylP2vXoKuO4/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuucmJbGwL_pNRg4-NyeCS6sB2AboJkg/s96-c/photo.jpg)](https://www.naukri.com/code360/profile/c694f727-7423-4538-b33f-656968a081ee)\nContributed by \nArshit \n216 upvotes \nAsked in companies\n![Microsoft](https://files.codingninjas.in/company-short-logo-url/14/a18b52c13a74e0d83f599b2be75d593b.png)![Facebook](https://files.codingninjas.in/company-short-logo-url/671/005b4926e308d9f0cac091529ae09b67.png)![Adobe](https://files.codingninjas.in/company-short-logo-url/21/abc1ca60ece68058fd182d8a8fa64086.png)\n##  Problem statement \nSend feedback \nYou are given a sorted array A consisting of N integers. Your task is to find the magic index in the given array.\n**Note :** ```\n1. A magic index in an array A[0 ... N - 1] is defined to be an index i such that A[i] = i.\n2. The elements in the array can be negative.\n3. The elements in the array can be repeated multiple times.\n4. There can be more than one magic index in an array.\n\n```\n\nDetailed explanation  ( Input/output format, Notes, Images ) \n**Input Format :** ```\nThe first line of the input contains an integer T denoting the number of test cases.\nThe first line of each test case contains one integer N, as described in the problem statement.\nThe second line of each test case contains N space-separated integers, representing the elements of the array.\n\n```\n**Output Format :** ```\nFor each test case print in a new line, one integer representing the magic index of the given array or -1 if there does not exist any magic index for the given array.\nIn case there is more than one magic index, return any of them.\n\n```\n\n**Constraints :** ```\n1 <= T <= 10\n1 <= N <= 10^5\n-10^9 <= A[i] <= 10^9\nTime Limit: 1sec\n\n```\n\n##### Sample Input 1 :\n```\n1\n5\n-5 -1 2 1 9\n\n```\n\n##### Sample Output 1 :\n```\n2\n\n```\n\n##### Explanation For Sample Input 1 :\n```\nThe output is 2 because A[2] = 2 and hence 2 is the magic index.\n\n```\n\n##### Sample Input 2 :\n```\n2\n5\n2 3 4 5 6\n6\n-1 -1 -1 4 4 4\n\n```\n\n##### Sample Output 2 :\n```\n-1\n4\n\n```\n\nC++ (g++ 5.4) \n![Full screen](https://static.naukimg.com/code360/assets/icons/controlled-timer.svg)\n1\n2\n3\n4\n5\n#include<bits/stdc++.h>\nint magicIndex(vector<int> a, int n) {\n// Write your code here\n}\nEnter to Rename, Shift+Enter to Preview\nConsole \nPrev \nRun  Submit code \nNext \nSettings\nReset Code\nLayouts\nFull Screen Mode\nStart timer\n",
