    "text": "![](https://www.naukri.com/code360/problems/longest-common-substring_1235207?interviewProblemRedirection=true&page=2&company%5B%5D=Salesforce&sort_entity=recents&sort_order=DESC) ![](https://static.naukimg.com/s/0/0/i/transparentImg.png)\n![Naukri Code 360](https://files.codingninjas.in/new-cn-logos-1-1711622387.svg)\n  * Learn\n\n\n  * Contests & Events\n\n\n  * Interview prep \n\n\n  * Practice\n\n\n  * Resources\n\n\nLogin\nInterview problemsView all problems\nProblem\nSubmissions\nHints & solutions\nDiscuss\n#  Longest Common Substring \nModerate \n![](https://files.codingninjas.in/yellow-spark-22969.svg)\n0/80 \nAverage time to solve is 25m \n[![profile](https://p.naukimg.com/jphotoV1/s244:LukcMTq83QYZEr+3VwgEbpw+x3Qgbcw6zybjyra0kmkTR6gqez4HPyiE)](https://www.naukri.com/code360/profile/7e85137a-3e8d-48e7-95e3-6ba8b32d4e01)\nContributed by \nDeep \n209 upvotes \nAsked in companies\n![Wells Fargo](https://files.codingninjas.in/company-short-logo-url/1839/6eaeed540dff1be3cf1691c377fb311d.png)![ShareChat](https://files.codingninjas.in/company-short-logo-url/3426/3f81c10c1b5322c48b42fd244cf15866.png)![Adobe](https://files.codingninjas.in/company-short-logo-url/21/abc1ca60ece68058fd182d8a8fa64086.png)\n##  Problem statement \nSend feedback \nYou are given two strings, _**'str1'**_ and _**'str2'**_. You have to find the length of the longest common substring.\nA substring is a continuous segment of a string. For example, \"bcd\" is a substring of \"abcd\", while \"acd\" or \"cda\" are not.\n**Example:** ```\nInput: ‘str1’ = “abcjklp” , ‘str2’ = “acjkp”.\nOutput: 3\nExplanation: The longest common substring between ‘str1’ and ‘str2’ is “cjk”, of length 3.\n\n```\n\nDetailed explanation  ( Input/output format, Notes, Images ) \n**Input Format:** ```\nThe First line of the test case contains the string ‘str1’.\nThe Second line contains the string ‘str2’.\n\n```\n**Output format:** ```\nReturn an integer representing the length of the longest common substring.\n\n```\n**Note:** ```\nYou don’t need to print anything. Just implement the given function.\n\n```\n\n##### Sample Input 1:\n```\nwasdijkl\nwsdjkl\n\n```\n\n##### Sample Output 1:\n```\n 3\n\n```\n\n##### Explanation Of Sample Input 1 :\n```\n The longest common substring is “jkl”, of length 3.\n\n```\n\n##### Sample Input 2:\n```\ntyfg\ncvbnuty\n\n```\n\n##### Sample Output 2:\n```\n2\n\n```\n\n##### Explanation Of Sample Input 2 :\n```\nThe longest common substring is “ty”, of length 2.\n\n```\n\n##### Expected time complexity:\n```\nThe expected time complexity is O(n*m),\nWhere ‘n’ and ‘m’ are the lengths of ‘st1’ and ‘str2’ respectively.\n\n```\n\n##### Constraints:\n```\n1 <= str1.length <= 1000\n1 <= str2.length <= 1000\n\n```\n\nC++ (g++ 5.4) \n![Full screen](https://static.naukimg.com/code360/assets/icons/controlled-timer.svg)\n1\n2\n3\n4\nint lcs(string &str1, string &str2){\n// Write your code here.\n}\nEnter to Rename, Shift+Enter to Preview\nConsole \nPrev \nRun  Submit code \nNext \nSettings\nReset Code\nLayouts\nFull Screen Mode\nStart timer\n",
