    "text": "![](https://www.naukri.com/code360/problems/concatenate-the-largest-digit_1263688?interviewProblemRedirection=true&page=2&company%5B%5D=Salesforce&sort_entity=recents&sort_order=DESC) ![](https://static.naukimg.com/s/0/0/i/transparentImg.png)\n![Naukri Code 360](https://files.codingninjas.in/new-cn-logos-1-1711622387.svg)\n  * Learn\n\n\n  * Contests & Events\n\n\n  * Interview prep \n\n\n  * Practice\n\n\n  * Resources\n\n\nLogin\nInterview problemsView all problems\nProblem\nSubmissions\nHints & solutions\nDiscuss\n#  Concatenate The Largest Digit \nEasy \n![](https://files.codingninjas.in/yellow-spark-22969.svg)\n0/40 \nAverage time to solve is 15m \n[![profile](https://p.naukimg.com/jphotoV1/s244:LukcMTm92wUZGLG0UQgEbpw2wHQlZ8w6zyZLS04jZft+q1tT3BlTv7bG)](https://www.naukri.com/code360/profile/ankitkharb)\nContributed by \nAnkit \n5 upvotes \nAsked in companies\n![Ola](https://files.codingninjas.in/company-short-logo-url/125/1b8b966b288e0184f83c464c04f0755c.png)![Salesforce](https://files.codingninjas.in/company-short-logo-url/30/794e491c9f0a68dadad41b6d36f66945.png)![CGI Inc.](https://files.codingninjas.in/96428d59a3d6729e223a493cb5b4e8ac.webp)\n##  Problem statement \nSend feedback \nYou are given three non-zero numbers ‘A’, ‘B’, and ‘C’. The task is to find the number formed by concatenating the largest digit from each of these numbers in the order of ‘A’, ‘B’, and ‘C’.\n**For Example :** ```\nA = 5678, B = 45 and C = 769\nThe largest digit in ‘A’ is ‘8’, ‘B’ is ‘5’, and ‘C’ is ‘9’. The new number formed by concatenating the largest digit from each of these numbers is ‘859’. So, the answer is ‘859’.\n\n```\n\nDetailed explanation  ( Input/output format, Notes, Images ) \n**Input Format :** ```\nThe first line of input contains an integer ‘T’ which denotes the number of test cases. Then, the ‘T’ test cases follow.\nThe first and only line of each test case contains three space-separated numbers, ‘A’, ‘B’, and ‘C’, denoting the given numbers.\n\n```\n**Output Format :** ```\nFor every test case, return the number formed by concatenating the largest digit from ‘A’, ‘B’, and ‘C’.\n\n```\n**Note :** ```\nYou do not need to print anything; it has already been taken care of. Just implement the function.\n\n```\n\n**Constraints :** ```\n1 <= T <= 10^4\n1 <= A, B, C <= 10^6\nTime limit: 1 Sec\n\n```\n\n#### Sample Input 1 :\n```\n2\n4554 292 123567\n90909 111 876\n\n```\n\n#### Sample Output 1 :\n```\n597\n918\n\n```\n\n#### Explanation Of Sample Input 1 :\n```\nTest Case 1:\na = 4554, b = 292 and c = 123567\nThe largest digit in ‘a’ is ‘5’, ‘b’ is ‘9’, and ‘c’ is ‘7’. The new number formed by concatenating the largest digit from each of these numbers is ‘597’. So, the answer is ‘597’. \nTest Case 2:\na = 90909, b = 111 and c = 876\nThe largest digit in ‘a’ is ‘9’, ‘b’ is ‘1’, and ‘c’ is ‘8’. The new number formed by concatenating the largest digit from each of these numbers is ‘918’. So, the answer is ‘918’.\n\n```\n\n#### Sample Input 2 :\n```\n2\n324865 123 456\n1 22 333\n\n```\n\n#### Sample Output 2 :\n```\n836\n123\n\n```\n\nC++ (g++ 5.4) \n![Full screen](https://static.naukimg.com/code360/assets/icons/controlled-timer.svg)\n1\n2\n3\n4\n#include<bits/stdc++.h>\nint concatLargestDigit(int a, int b, int c) {\n// Write your code here\n}\nEnter to Rename, Shift+Enter to Preview\nConsole \nPrev \nRun  Submit code \nNext \nSettings\nReset Code\nLayouts\nFull Screen Mode\nStart timer\n",
