    "text": "![](https://www.naukri.com/code360/problems/reaching-points_1214656?interviewProblemRedirection=true&page=2&company%5B%5D=Salesforce&sort_entity=recents&sort_order=DESC) ![](https://static.naukimg.com/s/0/0/i/transparentImg.png)\n![Naukri Code 360](https://files.codingninjas.in/new-cn-logos-1-1711622387.svg)\n  * Learn\n\n\n  * Contests & Events\n\n\n  * Interview prep \n\n\n  * Practice\n\n\n  * Resources\n\n\nLogin\nInterview problemsView all problems\nProblem\nSubmissions\nHints & solutions\nDiscuss\n#  Reaching Points \nModerate \n![](https://files.codingninjas.in/yellow-spark-22969.svg)\n0/80 \nAverage time to solve is 30m \n21 upvotes \nAsked in companies\n![Goldman Sachs](https://files.codingninjas.in/company-short-logo-url/29/aeacd9c525d4781763b3e38ac94e9611.png)![Uber](https://files.codingninjas.in/company-short-logo-url/776/2ab7f1d4a1d4cb7376d6a1ddc96a8016.png)![Salesforce](https://files.codingninjas.in/company-short-logo-url/30/794e491c9f0a68dadad41b6d36f66945.png)\n##  Problem statement \nSend feedback \nGiven a starting point (startX, startY) and target point(endX, endY) . Return true if there is a sequence of moves to transform the starting point into the ending point. In one move you can transform (x, y) to either (x + y, y) or (x, x + y).\nDetailed explanation  ( Input/output format, Notes, Images ) \n**Input Format** ```\nThe first line of input contains an integer ‘T’ denoting the number of test cases.\nThe next ‘T’ lines represent the test cases.\nThe first and the only line of each test case contains 4 integers startX,startY,endX, and endY.\n\n```\n**Output Format** ```\nFor each test case, print true if there is a sequence of moves to transform the starting point into the ending point, otherwise print false.\n\n```\n**Note:** ```\nYou do not need to print anything, it has already been taken care of. Just implement the given function.\n\n```\n\n**Constraints** ```\n1 <= ’T’ <= 50\n1 <= ’startX’, ’startY’, ’targetX’, ’targetY’ <= 10^9\n‘startX’, ’startY’ denotes starting coordinates.\n‘endX’, ’endY’ denotes target coordinates. \nTime Limit: 1 sec\n\n```\n\n##### Sample Input 1\n```\n2\n1 1 5 8\n3 5 7 9\n\n```\n\n##### Sample Output 1:\n```\ntrue \nfalse \n\n```\n\n#### Explanation For Sample Input 1:\n```\nFor the first test case, the sequence of moves\n(1,1)->(2,1)\n(2,1)->(2,3)\n(2,3)->(5,3)\n(5,3)->(5,8)\nHence the answer for this case is true.\nFor the second test case, there is not a possible sequence to reach the final points.\n\n```\n\n##### Sample Input 2\n```\n2\n1 1 1 1000\n1 1 1000 1\n\n```\n\n##### Sample Output 2\n```\ntrue\ntrue\n\n```\n\nC++ (g++ 5.4) \n![Full screen](https://static.naukimg.com/code360/assets/icons/controlled-timer.svg)\n1\n2\n3\n4\nbool isReachable(int startX, int startY, int endX, int endY) {\n// Write your code here.\n}\nEnter to Rename, Shift+Enter to Preview\nConsole \nPrev \nRun  Submit code \nNext \nSettings\nReset Code\nLayouts\nFull Screen Mode\nStart timer\n",
