    "text": "![](https://www.naukri.com/code360/problems/construct-the-lexicographically-largest-valid-sequence_1233105?interviewProblemRedirection=true&page=2&company%5B%5D=Salesforce&sort_entity=recents&sort_order=DESC) ![](https://static.naukimg.com/s/0/0/i/transparentImg.png)\n![Naukri Code 360](https://files.codingninjas.in/new-cn-logos-1-1711622387.svg)\n  * Learn\n\n\n  * Contests & Events\n\n\n  * Interview prep \n\n\n  * Practice\n\n\n  * Resources\n\n\nLogin\nInterview problemsView all problems\nProblem\nSubmissions\nHints & solutions\nDiscuss\n#  Construct the Lexicographically Largest Valid Sequence \nModerate \n![](https://files.codingninjas.in/yellow-spark-22969.svg)\n0/80 \nAverage time to solve is 35m \n[![profile](https://p.naukimg.com/jphotoV1/s244:LukcMTq82gIcG7+5XQgEbpw0xXUha8w6zyb0Kslsr4XKek1YQY2fB2lb)](https://www.naukri.com/code360/profile/5357c84b-e3f5-4f01-9159-ec0f8973946b)\nContributed by \nShrey \n12 upvotes \nAsked in companies\n![Salesforce](https://files.codingninjas.in/company-short-logo-url/30/794e491c9f0a68dadad41b6d36f66945.png)![Microsoft](https://files.codingninjas.in/company-short-logo-url/14/a18b52c13a74e0d83f599b2be75d593b.png)\n##  Problem statement \nSend feedback \nYou are given a positive integer N. Your task is to create the lexicographically largest sequence of length 2*N - 1 containing integers between 1 to N such that:\n```\n1. 1 occurs in the sequence exactly once.\n2. Each integer between 2 to N(inclusive) occurs in the sequence exactly twice.\n3. For each integer i between 2 to N, the distance between the two occurrences of i should be exactly i.\n\n```\n\nNote:\n```\n1. A sequence A is lexicographically larger than a sequence B (of the same length), if in the first position where A and B differ, sequence A has a number greater than the corresponding number in B.\n2. It is guaranteed that under the given constraints, there is always a solution. \n\n```\n\nDetailed explanation  ( Input/output format, Notes, Images ) \n**Input Format:** ```\nThe first line contains an integer, ‘T’ which denotes the number of test cases or queries to be run. Then, the T test cases follow.\nThe first and the only line of each test case contains one integer N, as described in the problem statement.\n\n```\n**Output Format:** ```\nFor each test case, print in a new line, 2*'N' - 1 space-separated integer representing the lexicographically largest sequence for the given input.\n\n```\n**Note:** ```\nYou do not need to print anything. It has already been taken care of. Just implement the given function.\n\n```\n\n**Constraints:** ```\n1 <= T <= 100\n1 <= N <= 20\nTime Limit: 1 second\n\n```\n\n##### Sample Input 1:\n```\n1\n2\n\n```\n\n##### Sample Output 1:\n```\n2 1 2\n\n```\n\n##### Explanation Of Sample Input 1:\n```\nIn test case 1: Since 1 occurs exactly once and 2 occurs exactly twice, and the distance between the two occurrences of 2 is 2. The sequence {2,1,2} is also the lexicographically largest sequence possible that satisfies the given condition.\n\n```\n\n##### Sample Input 2:\n```\n1\n3\n\n```\n\n##### Sample Output 2:\n```\n3 1 2 3 2\n\n```\n\n##### Explanation Of Sample Input 2:\n```\nIn test case 1: [3, 1, 2, 3, 2] is the largest lexicographically sequence which we need.\n\n```\n\nC++ (g++ 5.4) \n![Full screen](https://static.naukimg.com/code360/assets/icons/controlled-timer.svg)\n1\n2\n3\nvector<int> validSequence(int n) {\n// Write your code here.\n}\nEnter to Rename, Shift+Enter to Preview\nConsole \nPrev \nRun  Submit code \nNext \nSettings\nReset Code\nLayouts\nFull Screen Mode\nStart timer\n",
