    "text": "![](https://www.naukri.com/code360/problems/balanced-sequence-after-replacement_1115685?interviewProblemRedirection=true&page=2&company%5B%5D=Visa&sort_entity=recents&sort_order=DESC) ![](https://static.naukimg.com/s/0/0/i/transparentImg.png)\n![Naukri Code 360](https://files.codingninjas.in/new-cn-logos-1-1711622387.svg)\n  * Learn\n\n\n  * Contests & Events\n\n\n  * Interview prep \n\n\n  * Practice\n\n\n  * Resources\n\n\nLogin\nInterview problemsView all problems\nProblem\nSubmissions\nHints & solutions\nDiscuss\n#  Balanced Sequence After Replacement \nEasy \n![](https://files.codingninjas.in/yellow-spark-22969.svg)\n0/40 \nAverage time to solve is 15m \n[![profile](https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-Fq4O0_6_JQY/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/ACHi3rdW32GmcLOpLF_p_xVI41mMy7Vtvg/s96-c/photo.jpg)](https://www.naukri.com/code360/profile/d04967a1-c368-4064-98db-dcab53123432)\nContributed by \nPankaj \n7 upvotes \nAsked in companies\n![Visa](https://files.codingninjas.in/company-short-logo-url/38/d1bbf452a8f8fdb85ac92821f0cd6fb3.png)![Ola](https://files.codingninjas.in/company-short-logo-url/125/1b8b966b288e0184f83c464c04f0755c.png)\n##  Problem statement \nSend feedback \nYou are given a string of length ‘N’ containing only the following characters: ‘[’, ‘{’, ‘(’, ‘)’, ‘}’, ‘]’. At some places, there is ‘X’ in place of any bracket. Your task is to determine that if you replace all the X’s with appropriate brackets, is it possible to get a valid balanced sequence or not.\nFor example:\n```\nFor the given string “[X)](X”, the possible replacement for the first X is ‘(‘ and the second X is ‘)’, which makes the sequence “[()]()”, which is a valid balanced sequence. \nFor the given string “[XX{”, there is no possible replacement for X which can make it a valid bracket sequence. \n\n```\n\nDetailed explanation  ( Input/output format, Notes, Images ) \n**Input format:** ```\nThe first line contains an integer 'T' which denotes the number of test cases or queries to be run. Then, the T test cases follow.\nThe first and only line of each test case or query contains the string. \n\n```\n**Output format:** ```\nFor each test case, print “Valid” if a balanced sequence is possible, otherwise, print “Invalid”, without quotes in a separate line.\n\n```\n\nNote:\n```\nYou do not need to print anything, it has already been taken care of. Just return 'True' for valid string and 'False' for an invalid string.\n\n```\n\n**Constraints:** ```\n1 <= T <= 10 \n1 <= N <= 20 \nTime limit: 1 sec\n\n```\n\n##### Sample input 1:\n```\n2\n{[X(X)]}\n{[X](X)}\n\n```\n\n##### Sample output 1:\n```\nValid\nInvalid\n\n```\n\n##### Explanation\n```\nFor test case 1: \nThe correct valid bracket sequence is: { [ ( ( ) ) ] } \nFor test case 2: \nNo valid bracket sequence is possible. \n\n```\n\n##### Sample input 2:\n```\n2\n[(X){}{{}}]\nXX\n\n```\n\n##### Sample output 2:\n```\nInvalid\nValid\n\n```\n\nC++ (g++ 5.4) \n![Full screen](https://static.naukimg.com/code360/assets/icons/controlled-timer.svg)\n1\n2\n3\n4\n5\n6\n#include<bits/stdc++.h>\nbool isValid(string &str)\n{\n// Write your code here.\n}\nEnter to Rename, Shift+Enter to Preview\nConsole \nPrev \nRun  Submit code \nNext \nSettings\nReset Code\nLayouts\nFull Screen Mode\nStart timer\n",
