    "text": "![](https://www.naukri.com/code360/problems/find-the-character_2410404?interviewProblemRedirection=true&page=2&company%5B%5D=Uber&sort_entity=recents&sort_order=DESC) ![](https://static.naukimg.com/s/0/0/i/transparentImg.png)\n![Naukri Code 360](https://files.codingninjas.in/new-cn-logos-1-1711622387.svg)\n  * Learn\n\n\n  * Contests & Events\n\n\n  * Interview prep \n\n\n  * Practice\n\n\n  * Resources\n\n\nLogin\nInterview problemsView all problems\nProblem\nSubmissions\nHints & solutions\nDiscuss\n#  Find the character \nModerate \n![](https://files.codingninjas.in/yellow-spark-22969.svg)\n0/80 \n[![profile](https://files.codingninjas.in/avatar-1710924338.png)](https://www.naukri.com/code360/profile/srejanbera)\nContributed by \nSrejan \n0 upvote \nAsked in companies\n![Uber](https://files.codingninjas.in/company-short-logo-url/776/2ab7f1d4a1d4cb7376d6a1ddc96a8016.png)![Caterpillar Inc](https://files.codingninjas.in/caterpillar_inc_logo-1-34006.webp)\n##  Problem statement \nSend feedback \nTwo strings ‘A’ and ‘B’ are given. A string ‘C’ has to be formed using these two strings according to the following rules:\n```\n1. Append string ‘A’ to C one time.\n2. Append string ‘B’ to C two times.\n3. Append string ‘A’ to C three times.\n4. Append string ‘B’ to C four times.\n5. Append string ‘A’ to C five times.\nAnd so on…. \n\n```\n\nYour task is to return the ‘K’th character to the newly formed string ‘C’.\n**For Example** ```\nIf ‘A’ = “AB” and B = “CD” and K = 7.\nThe formed string will be “ABCDCDABABAB…...”.\nSo, the 7th character is A.\n\n```\n\nDetailed explanation  ( Input/output format, Notes, Images ) \n**Input Format:** ```\nThe first line of the input contains an integer, 'T,’ denoting the number of test cases.\nThe first line of each test case contains two strings, 'A’ and ’B’.\nThe second line contains ‘K’ representing the character number to be found.\n\n```\n**Output Format:** ```\nFor each test case, print a character denoting the ‘K’th character.\nPrint the output of each test case in a separate line.\n\n```\n**Note:** ```\nYou do not need to print anything. It has already been taken care of. Just implement the given function.\n\n```\n\n**Constraints:** ```\n1 <= T <= 10\n1 <= length of ‘A’,length of ‘B’ <= 100.\n1 <= ‘K’ <= 10^15\n\nTime limit: 1 sec\n\n```\n\n##### Sample Input 1:\n```\n2\nAB\nCD\n7\nABC\nA\n10\n\n```\n\n##### Sample Output 1:\n```\nA\nB\n\n```\n\n##### Explanation of sample input 1:\n```\nFor the first test case,\nThe formed string will be “ABCDCDABABABCDCDCDCD…...”.\nThe 7th character is A. Hence, the answer is A.\nFor the second test case:\nThe formed string will be “ABCAAABCABCABCAAAA……..” .\nThe 10th character is B. Hence, the answer is B.\n\n```\n\n##### Sample Input 2:\n```\n2\nABCDD\nF\n6\nACE\nX\n3\n\n```\n\n##### Sample Output 2:\n```\nF \nE\n\n```\n\nC++ (g++ 5.4) \n![Full screen](https://static.naukimg.com/code360/assets/icons/controlled-timer.svg)\n1\n2\n3\n4\nint findTheCharacter(string &a, string &b, int k)\n{\n// Write your code here.\n}\nEnter to Rename, Shift+Enter to Preview\nConsole \nPrev \nRun  Submit code \nNext \nSettings\nReset Code\nLayouts\nFull Screen Mode\nStart timer\n",
