    "text": "![](https://www.naukri.com/code360/problems/max-sum-matrix_2421455?interviewProblemRedirection=true&page=2&company%5B%5D=Uber&sort_entity=recents&sort_order=DESC) ![](https://static.naukimg.com/s/0/0/i/transparentImg.png)\n![Naukri Code 360](https://files.codingninjas.in/new-cn-logos-1-1711622387.svg)\n  * Learn\n\n\n  * Contests & Events\n\n\n  * Interview prep \n\n\n  * Practice\n\n\n  * Resources\n\n\nLogin\nInterview problemsView all problems\nProblem\nSubmissions\nHints & solutions\nDiscuss\n#  Max Sum Matrix \nModerate \n![](https://files.codingninjas.in/yellow-spark-22969.svg)\n0/80 \n[![profile](https://p.naukimg.com/jphotoV1/s244:LukcMTq+1gseHruzUQgEbpw3xHQhb8w6zyaEx79fK/64gui3B+67M5Ui)](https://www.naukri.com/code360/profile/c6518811-e004-425c-aaa8-d257e0a961d2)\nContributed by \nHARSHAD \n3 upvotes \nAsked in companies\n![Uber](https://files.codingninjas.in/company-short-logo-url/776/2ab7f1d4a1d4cb7376d6a1ddc96a8016.png)![D.E.Shaw](https://files.codingninjas.in/asset_0000000000001257_1684871463_DE%2520Shaw.png)\n##  Problem statement \nSend feedback \nYou are given a matrix “mat” of size ‘m’ * ‘n’ and an integer “val”. You need to find the maximum length of the side of a square having sum not greater than “val”.\nIf there is no such square, return 0.\n**For Example :** ```\nm = 4, n = 3, mat = {{1, 1, 1}, {2, 1, 2}, {1, 2, 1}, {1, 1, 1}}, val = 5.\n\n```\n\n![](https://files.codingninjas.in/max_sum_matrix_example_1-12839.png)\n```\nIn this example, the maximum value of length of side which can be obtained is 2, Having the starting index: {0, 0} or {0, 1} or {2, 0} or {2, 1}.\n\n```\n\nDetailed explanation  ( Input/output format, Notes, Images ) \n**Input Format :** ```\nThe first line contains a single integer ‘T’ denoting the number of test cases, then each test case follows:\nThe first line of each test case contains two integers ‘n’ and ‘m’ denoting the dimensions of the matrix.\nThe next ‘n’ lines contain ‘m’ integer where the jth integer of the ith line denotes the value at “mat[i][j]”.\nThe next line contains a single integer “val” denoting the maximum sum needed.\n\n```\n**Output Format :** ```\nFor each test case, print a single integer “ans” denoting the maximum side of the square.\nOutput for each test case will be printed in a separate line.\n\n```\n**Note :** ```\nYou are not required to print anything; it has already been taken care of. Just implement the function.\n\n```\n\n**Constraints :** ```\n1 <= T <= 10  \n1 <= N, M <= 300\n1 <= mat[i][j] <= 5000\n1 <= val <= 50000\nTime limit: 1 sec\n\n```\n\n##### Sample Input 1 :\n```\n2\n4 2\n1 1\n1 1\n1 1\n1 1\n25\n3 3\n3 3 3\n3 1 3\n3 3 3\n2\n\n```\n\n##### Sample Output 1 :\n```\n2\n1\n\n```\n\n##### Explanation For Sample Input 1 :\n```\nIn the first test case, val is high enough, so we can take a square of the maximum side, which is 2.\nHence the answer is 2.\nIn the second test case, val is 2, hence the only square matrix having the sum of value less than 2 is {{1}}, having side equal to 1.\nHence the answer is 1.\n\n```\n\n##### Sample Input 2 :\n```\n2\n1 5\n1 4 2 3 4\n100\n6 4\n1 8 7 3\n4 2 9 7\n1 2 7 1\n88 5 4 11\n4 2 6 2\n8 45 66 5\n11\n\n```\n\n##### Sample Output 2 :\n```\n1\n2\n\n```\n\nC++ (g++ 5.4) \n![Full screen](https://static.naukimg.com/code360/assets/icons/controlled-timer.svg)\n1\n2\n3\n4\nint maxSumMatrix(int n, int m, vector<vector<int>> &mat, int val) {\n// Write your code here.\n}\nEnter to Rename, Shift+Enter to Preview\nConsole \nPrev \nRun  Submit code \nNext \nSettings\nReset Code\nLayouts\nFull Screen Mode\nStart timer\n",
