    "text": "![](https://www.naukri.com/code360/problems/detect-cycle-in-a-directed-graph_920545?interviewProblemRedirection=true&page=2&company%5B%5D=American+Express&sort_entity=recents&sort_order=DESC) ![](https://static.naukimg.com/s/0/0/i/transparentImg.png)\n![Naukri Code 360](https://files.codingninjas.in/new-cn-logos-1-1711622387.svg)\n  * Learn\n\n\n  * Contests & Events\n\n\n  * Interview prep \n\n\n  * Practice\n\n\n  * Resources\n\n\nLogin\nInterview problemsView all problems\nProblem\nSubmissions\nHints & solutions\nDiscuss\n#  Detect Cycle in a Directed Graph \nModerate \n![](https://files.codingninjas.in/yellow-spark-22969.svg)\n0/80 \nAverage time to solve is 25m \n[![profile](https://files.codingninjas.in/avatar-1710924338.png)](https://www.naukri.com/code360/profile/null)\nContributed by \nArshit \n60 upvotes \nAsked in companies\n![Flipkart](https://files.codingninjas.in/company-short-logo-url/16/89419331b9f7e550a189bd4ba51ca9ce.png)![Amazon](https://files.codingninjas.in/company-short-logo-url/2/731aacbd5ef5e7c6d6195f96525fdc79.png)![American Express](https://files.codingninjas.in/company-short-logo-url/42/3e977fa248f0de6f0458b7e0a189153f.png)\n##  Problem statement \nSend feedback \nGiven a directed graph, check whether the graph contains a cycle or not. Your function should return true if the given graph contains at least one cycle, else return false.\nDetailed explanation  ( Input/output format, Notes, Images ) \n**Input Format:** ```\nThe first line of input contains an integer T, the number of test cases.\nThe first line of each test case contains two single space-separated integers ‘V’, and ‘E’. ‘V’ represents the number of nodes and ‘E’ represents the number of edges in the graph.\nFrom the second line onwards of each test case, the next 'E' lines will denote the edges of the graph where every edge is defined by two single space-separated integers 'A' and 'B', which signifies an edge from vertex 'A’ to vertex 'B'.\n\n```\n**Output Format:** ```\nFor each test case print \"true\" if a cycle exists, else \"false\".\n\n```\n\n**Constraints:** ```\n1 <= T <= 10\n1 <= V <= 10^3\n0 <= E <= 10^3\n0 <= A, B < V\nTime Limit: 1 sec\n\n```\n\n##### Sample Input 1:.\n```\n2\n4 4\n0 1\n1 2\n2 3\n3 0\n3 3\n1 0\n1 2\n0 2\n\n```\n\n##### Sample Output 1:\n```\ntrue\nfalse\n\n```\n\n##### Explanation for Sample Input 1:\n```\nIn the first case,\nFrom node 0 we can reach 0 again by following this sequence of nodes in the path: 0,1,2,3,0. As we can see in the image below.\n\n```\n\n![Example](https://files.codingninjas.in/testcase-1-9946.jpeg)\n```\nIn the second case,\nThere is no cycle in the given graph. As we can see in the image below.\n\n```\n\n![Example](https://files.codingninjas.in/testcase-2-9947.jpeg)\n##### Sample Input 2:\n```\n2\n3 2\n0 1\n0 2\n3 3\n1 1\n0 2\n1 2\n\n```\n\n##### Sample Output 2:\n```\nfalse\ntrue\n\n```\n\nC++ (g++ 5.4) \n![Full screen](https://static.naukimg.com/code360/assets/icons/controlled-timer.svg)\n1\n2\n3\n4\n5\nbool isCyclic(vector<vector<int>>& edges, int v, int e)\n{\n// Write your code here\n}\nEnter to Rename, Shift+Enter to Preview\nConsole \nPrev \nRun  Submit code \nNext \nSettings\nReset Code\nLayouts\nFull Screen Mode\nStart timer\n",
