    "text": "![](https://www.naukri.com/code360/problems/reverse-of-a-number_893271?interviewProblemRedirection=true&page=2&company%5B%5D=Wells+Fargo&sort_entity=recents&sort_order=DESC) ![](https://static.naukimg.com/s/0/0/i/transparentImg.png)\n![Naukri Code 360](https://files.codingninjas.in/new-cn-logos-1-1711622387.svg)\n  * Learn\n\n\n  * Contests & Events\n\n\n  * Interview prep \n\n\n  * Practice\n\n\n  * Resources\n\n\nLogin\nInterview problemsView all problems\nProblem\nSubmissions\nHints & solutions\nDiscuss\n#  Reverse Number \nEasy \n![](https://files.codingninjas.in/yellow-spark-22969.svg)\n0/40 \nAverage time to solve is 10m \n[![profile](https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gia0y_xz5X8uvbcMZaZOBi08bIcXGxyAeB4aQiHpg=s96-c)](https://www.naukri.com/code360/profile/6158b977-4836-4d53-b260-987ff599fac7)\nContributed by \nAditya \n77 upvotes \nAsked in companies\n![Cognizant](https://files.codingninjas.in/company-short-logo-url/841/90c29fb8e0b9ac9c35cb527aac3d990d.png)![Tata Consultancy Services \\(TCS\\)](https://files.codingninjas.in/company-short-logo-url/885/1b107798c82fea68d11a1b7c75ee70a1.png)![Accenture](https://files.codingninjas.in/company-short-logo-url/57/f51594f9664e34708bb61c55d79c1fc0.png)\n##  Problem statement \nSend feedback \nNinja is feeling very bored and wants to try something new. So, he decides to find the reverse of a given number. But he cannot do it on his own and needs your help.\nNote:\n```\nIf a number has trailing zeros, then its reverse will not include them. For e.g., the reverse of 10400 will be 401 instead of 00401.\n\n```\n\nDetailed explanation  ( Input/output format, Notes, Images ) \nInput Format:\n```\nThe first line contains an integer 'T' which denotes the number of test cases or queries to be run.\nThe first line of each test case contains one integer ‘N’ denoting the given number.\n\n```\n\nOutput Format:\n```\nFor each case, you need to print the reverse of the given number.\nThe output of each test case will be printed on a separate line.\n\n```\n\nNote:\n```\nYou do not need to input or print anything, it has already been taken care of. Just implement the given function.\n\n```\n\nConstraints:\n```\n1 <= T <= 5\n1 <= N <= 10 ^ 18\nTime Limit = 1 sec\n\n```\n\n#### Sample Input 1:\n```\n2\n10400\n12345\n\n```\n\n#### Sample Output 1:\n```\n401\n54321\n\n```\n\n#### Explanation of Sample Input 1:\n```\nTest case 1:\nFor the first test case of sample output 1, as the number is ‘10400’, after finding the reverse, it turns out to be ‘00401’ but we need to leave the trailing zeros. Therefore our solution is 401\nTest case 2:  \nFor the second test case of sample output 1, as the number is ‘12345’, the reverse will be ‘54321’\n\n```\n\n#### Sample Input 2:\n```\n2\n1000\n7654321\n\n```\n\n#### Sample Output 2:\n```\n1\n1234567\n\n```\n\n#### Explanation of Sample Input 2:\n```\nTest case 1:\nFor the first test case of sample output 2, as the input number is ‘1000’, we get the reverse as ‘1’.\nTest case 2:  \nFor the second test case of sample output 2, as the input number is ‘7654321’, we get the reverse as ‘1234567’.\n\n```\n\nC++ (g++ 5.4) \n![Full screen](https://static.naukimg.com/code360/assets/icons/controlled-timer.svg)\n1\n2\n3\n4\n5\n6\n#include<bits/stdc++.h>\nlonglongint reverseNumber(longlongint n)\n{\n//type your code here\n}\nEnter to Rename, Shift+Enter to Preview\nConsole \nPrev \nRun  Submit code \nNext \nSettings\nReset Code\nLayouts\nFull Screen Mode\nStart timer\n",
